WEBVTT

00:50.049 --> 00:51.134
ALL FIGURES,
INCIDENTS, LOCATIONS,

00:51.217 --> 00:52.469
ORGANIZATIONS,
AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS.

00:52.552 --> 00:53.970
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

00:54.054 --> 00:54.971
IN ACCORDANCE WITH GUIDELINES.

01:01.269 --> 01:02.771
Where's patient Shin I-rang?

01:02.854 --> 01:04.397
Are you Mr. Shin I-rang's guardian?

01:04.481 --> 01:05.482
Yes.

01:05.565 --> 01:07.150
I'm sorry.

01:07.233 --> 01:10.195
He was already unconscious
when he arrived at the hospital.

01:23.333 --> 01:24.501
No.

01:33.968 --> 01:35.345
I should've been there.

01:39.057 --> 01:41.643
I should've been with him.

02:30.817 --> 02:31.776
What…

02:33.027 --> 02:34.279
Am I…

02:34.988 --> 02:36.489
Am I dead?

02:42.912 --> 02:43.913
Am I…

02:45.999 --> 02:48.001
dead for real?

02:51.129 --> 02:52.422
Mister.

02:55.216 --> 02:56.593
Who are you?

02:57.760 --> 02:58.678
Wait.

02:59.846 --> 03:01.180
Who am I?

03:01.723 --> 03:02.849
Mister.

03:04.517 --> 03:05.977
You have to go there.

03:08.605 --> 03:11.316
Where is there?

03:16.154 --> 03:17.655
Mother, he's here!

03:27.707 --> 03:30.960
I-rang.

03:31.044 --> 03:33.004
I-rang, Mom is here.

03:33.922 --> 03:36.966
Doctor, what happened to my son?

03:54.192 --> 03:55.818
Don't go out there.

03:58.780 --> 04:01.407
Mister, don't go.

04:04.035 --> 04:06.037
What happened to my son, doctor?

04:06.955 --> 04:09.624
Please. Please help him, doctor.

04:09.707 --> 04:12.502
We've already tried CPR several times.

04:12.585 --> 04:15.296
-Doctor.
-Please. I beg you.

04:17.298 --> 04:18.841
You said…

04:20.760 --> 04:22.595
you'd find my mom for me.

04:32.146 --> 04:37.026
Patient Shin I-rang is pronounced dead
at 8:43 p.m. on August 16…

04:38.027 --> 04:40.488
What… Did you hear that?

04:40.571 --> 04:42.407
-Get the defibrillator.
-Yes, doctor.

04:42.490 --> 04:44.492
-What's going on…
-Please move aside.

04:44.575 --> 04:46.995
-No.
-Folks, please move back.

04:47.078 --> 04:48.621
-But…
-Come this way.

04:48.705 --> 04:49.872
I-rang.

04:50.373 --> 04:51.374
Clear!

04:52.792 --> 04:53.918
Charge to 200 joules.

05:06.514 --> 05:07.974
EKG has returned!

05:14.314 --> 05:16.816
-I-rang, can you see me?
-I-rang.

05:17.483 --> 05:18.985
I-rang, can you hear me?

05:26.159 --> 05:27.493
Attorney Shin…

05:47.305 --> 05:48.431
…Reporter Park Seong-chan.

05:49.348 --> 05:53.478
We will bring you more updates on Cho
as the story develops.

05:53.561 --> 05:57.857
Next, let's meet the hero
who saved the kidnapped child, Kwon.

05:57.940 --> 05:59.776
-Reporter Kim Bo-ra?
-There it comes.

05:59.859 --> 06:02.820
I'm currently at the hospital
where Mr. Shin I-rang is hospitalized.

06:02.904 --> 06:06.157
Mr. Shin got shot in the process
of saving the child,

06:06.240 --> 06:08.367
-but he's undergoing a smooth recovery--
-He's coming out.

06:08.910 --> 06:11.496
-Mr. Shin is coming out now.
-Mr. Shin!

06:20.838 --> 06:22.048
A word, please!

06:27.136 --> 06:30.139
Lightning…

06:46.447 --> 06:48.574
Lightning…

06:55.456 --> 06:57.750
Uncle.

06:57.834 --> 07:00.419
You're so cool. You're the best!

07:02.547 --> 07:03.381
You think?

07:04.215 --> 07:07.802
If you say so, I guess I really am cool.

07:08.469 --> 07:09.595
What a relief.

07:10.304 --> 07:11.431
-Ouch!
-Oh, no.

07:11.514 --> 07:13.516
-Are you okay?
-Careful.

07:17.311 --> 07:19.355
-That fool.
-Get some rest, okay?

07:20.273 --> 07:22.233
-Thanks, everyone.
-See you later.

07:22.817 --> 07:24.652
Bong-su, power!

07:25.319 --> 07:27.029
I-rang, power!

07:29.240 --> 07:32.368
-Let's go.
-Gosh, you've been through a lot.

07:32.452 --> 07:34.328
Have some time alone. We'll be back soon.

07:41.002 --> 07:42.378
Attorney Han cried?

07:42.462 --> 07:47.133
She cried her eyes out,
saying she should've been with you.

07:48.050 --> 07:49.594
She did?

07:52.972 --> 07:54.599
She cried her eyes out?

08:00.313 --> 08:01.772
What's so funny?

08:01.856 --> 08:03.649
Oh, Attorney Han.

08:06.277 --> 08:07.361
Are you okay?

08:07.945 --> 08:10.156
Why can't you be more careful?
You got shot.

08:11.657 --> 08:13.034
I'm okay. I mean it.

08:18.080 --> 08:20.541
Mister, can I go to your house?

08:21.584 --> 08:25.755
Do that. It must be boring to stay here.
Go have fun with Da-bong and her grandma.

08:26.589 --> 08:27.673
Okay!

08:28.174 --> 08:29.842
Yay!

08:34.013 --> 08:35.681
Si-ho left.

08:43.314 --> 08:45.900
You must've been shocked because of me.

08:47.401 --> 08:49.487
I was shocked and upset.

08:51.989 --> 08:55.576
You should've gone with Bong-su or me
to handle such a thing.

08:55.660 --> 08:57.411
It was dangerous to go there alone.

08:57.995 --> 08:59.163
You're right.

09:00.039 --> 09:01.999
I guess I was in a rush.

09:02.917 --> 09:06.921
I wanted to find out who Si-ho was
as soon as possible.

09:10.091 --> 09:11.175
Oh, right.

09:12.134 --> 09:14.720
The day you went to find Si-ho,

09:14.804 --> 09:18.057
his dad visited the office
for a divorce consultation.

09:18.975 --> 09:20.393
Divorce?

09:20.476 --> 09:22.436
They've been living apart
since Si-ho went missing.

09:23.312 --> 09:27.233
Both of them are struggling with regret
and a sense of guilt.

09:28.025 --> 09:31.654
They don't even know if he's alive.
I bet it's worse for them.

09:32.238 --> 09:33.239
You're right.

09:34.574 --> 09:36.075
A slim chance

09:36.993 --> 09:38.703
can cause more pain sometimes.

09:41.872 --> 09:44.959
Anyway, how's the investigation going?

09:45.710 --> 09:47.753
It's taking place under detention

09:47.837 --> 09:49.922
thanks to Ye-jun
who was rescued from the scene.

09:50.840 --> 09:54.176
But Cho Chi-yeong is pleading the Fifth
regarding Si-ho

09:54.260 --> 09:56.053
who went missing more than a year ago.

09:57.221 --> 09:59.432
Ye-jun and Si-ho are around the same age

09:59.515 --> 10:03.227
and were both in yellow rain boots.

10:04.020 --> 10:07.064
Nevertheless, no evidence proves
that he kidnapped Si-ho.

10:10.985 --> 10:11.986
What are you doing?

10:12.737 --> 10:15.406
A sentence for abduction, enticement,
and confinement of a minor

10:15.489 --> 10:17.450
is only a max sentence
of ten years in prison.

10:17.533 --> 10:19.660
It'll be a much lighter sentence
in reality.

10:20.328 --> 10:21.621
I can't let that happen.

10:24.123 --> 10:25.416
I'll help you like this.

10:26.375 --> 10:29.253
-Oh, gosh.
-I-rang was shot!

10:29.337 --> 10:30.338
Sorry. My bad.

10:31.547 --> 10:32.757
At least, let's walk in step.

10:32.840 --> 10:34.342
Left foot, left foot.

10:34.425 --> 10:36.636
What for? We're not soldiers.

10:37.261 --> 10:38.095
Oops!

10:38.179 --> 10:39.096
Oh, come on!

10:40.056 --> 10:41.932
Are you okay?

10:46.854 --> 10:48.439
"I slept like a baby."

10:48.522 --> 10:50.483
"Did you sleep well?"

10:50.566 --> 10:52.318
I wish I could play too.

10:52.943 --> 10:54.445
"Honey, did you have a good night?"

10:54.528 --> 10:55.488
"Of course."

10:57.323 --> 10:59.158
"We should have breakfast."

10:59.241 --> 11:01.535
"Let's have breakfast and…"

11:01.619 --> 11:04.413
"Honey, do you have an acting gig today?"

11:05.373 --> 11:08.125
"Yes, I play a doctor role today."

11:08.209 --> 11:10.753
"My gosh, that's amazing."

11:11.837 --> 11:14.382
Dad, can you not go to work?

11:15.091 --> 11:16.926
I want to spend time with you.

11:17.510 --> 11:20.012
"Should we go to the amusement park
with Da-bong this weekend?"

11:20.596 --> 11:23.641
"Nice idea. That's my wife, Sa-rang."

11:24.392 --> 11:25.976
I want to go camping.

11:26.060 --> 11:27.686
"Good luck with the shoot."

11:27.770 --> 11:29.647
"Okay, thanks."

11:38.531 --> 11:40.699
Excuse me.

11:40.783 --> 11:42.868
I'm here about the boy named Yoon Si-ho.

11:45.162 --> 11:47.373
Are you Si-ho's father?

11:49.166 --> 11:50.751
Do you know my son?

11:51.794 --> 11:53.212
I heard from the police.

11:54.171 --> 11:55.881
That he went missing a year ago.

12:00.344 --> 12:02.346
You saved the boy named Ye-jun.

12:03.514 --> 12:04.515
Do you

12:05.349 --> 12:08.894
happen to know where Si-ho is?

12:11.147 --> 12:12.148
No.

12:13.232 --> 12:14.442
I'm sorry.

12:17.736 --> 12:19.029
I see.

12:38.424 --> 12:39.383
Hello?

12:42.678 --> 12:43.804
He doesn't know.

12:46.307 --> 12:48.851
Honey? Are you okay?

12:49.977 --> 12:51.395
Do you want me to go there now?

12:55.024 --> 12:57.193
Okay, I'm sorry. I just…

12:58.694 --> 13:00.654
Our Si-ho will be okay.

13:01.363 --> 13:04.366
Let's wait a little more, okay?

13:10.998 --> 13:13.834
He said he'd let you in the police car?

13:15.169 --> 13:16.337
Yes.

13:17.004 --> 13:20.341
He was a stranger.
Weren't you scared of him?

13:20.925 --> 13:22.510
He wasn't a stranger.

13:23.052 --> 13:27.181
That detective gave
a safety lesson at school.

13:29.558 --> 13:32.770
In that case,
it must've been easier to trust him.

13:32.853 --> 13:36.065
And he was really good to me.

13:36.774 --> 13:40.069
He showed me his pistol
and played with me.

13:42.238 --> 13:46.659
But when I wanted to go home at night,

13:47.576 --> 13:51.622
he stopped me, saying he'd take me
somewhere fun the next day.

13:53.082 --> 13:57.002
I still said I was going to go home,

13:57.086 --> 13:58.546
and he got angry.

14:00.673 --> 14:02.007
The truth is,

14:02.675 --> 14:05.553
I had a headache since that morning.

14:07.513 --> 14:11.767
It got worse as he yelled at me.

14:13.644 --> 14:16.564
Did it hurt badly?

14:17.731 --> 14:18.732
Yes.

14:20.568 --> 14:21.902
So,

14:22.945 --> 14:25.072
I took medicine and kept sleeping.

14:25.781 --> 14:27.950
When I opened my eyes,

14:28.033 --> 14:29.994
I was in your office.

14:33.330 --> 14:34.290
I see.

14:39.503 --> 14:42.006
I miss my parents.

14:43.382 --> 14:45.009
Can't I go see them?

14:50.222 --> 14:51.056
Si-ho.

14:52.516 --> 14:55.769
I'm afraid you can't see your mom and dad

14:56.437 --> 14:57.521
right now.

14:58.772 --> 14:59.815
Why?

15:01.233 --> 15:02.443
Your parents are…

15:04.653 --> 15:06.405
a little sick.

15:07.531 --> 15:09.992
Really? How sick are they?

15:11.535 --> 15:13.120
They're heartsick.

15:14.663 --> 15:15.623
Why?

15:17.541 --> 15:18.751
Let's say

15:20.127 --> 15:22.963
your friend tripped next to you.

15:23.505 --> 15:25.633
How would you feel?

15:29.470 --> 15:31.013
I'd feel sorry

15:32.056 --> 15:33.599
for not stopping him from tripping.

15:34.767 --> 15:35.643
Right.

15:37.269 --> 15:41.482
You'd feel sorry
even if it weren't your fault.

15:42.441 --> 15:45.110
Your parents are feeling the same way.

15:48.530 --> 15:50.491
They couldn't protect you,

15:51.825 --> 15:53.702
their precious son.

15:55.537 --> 15:59.458
Thinking of what they could've done,

16:01.168 --> 16:02.920
they constantly blame themselves.

16:05.464 --> 16:06.423
That's why

16:07.549 --> 16:09.969
it makes them more and more heartsick.

16:10.678 --> 16:12.513
That's not good.

16:14.181 --> 16:17.559
How do you treat being heartsick?

16:18.394 --> 16:22.773
I want my mom and dad to be happy again.

16:26.735 --> 16:30.280
If they know that you're this okay,

16:31.073 --> 16:32.658
it might ease their pain a little.

16:35.285 --> 16:37.788
But they don't know.

16:39.331 --> 16:41.166
They can't see

16:41.917 --> 16:43.669
or hear me.

16:44.253 --> 16:45.629
Don't worry.

16:45.713 --> 16:47.339
I'll help you.

16:49.425 --> 16:50.384
Okay.

16:52.136 --> 16:53.053
Then…

17:03.105 --> 17:03.981
Whoosh.

17:05.065 --> 17:06.066
Whoosh.

17:16.452 --> 17:17.578
Let's go.

17:17.661 --> 17:18.787
Give me your briefcase.

17:23.125 --> 17:23.959
Wait.

17:24.043 --> 17:26.045
Oh, my! I'm sorry.

17:26.128 --> 17:28.922
-Knock it off!
-Okay, my bad.

17:36.972 --> 17:38.515
Hello. You came early.

17:39.099 --> 17:42.144
-How are you feeling?
-I'm okay. Let's get started.

17:44.730 --> 17:47.149
Cho Chi-yeong divorced his wife
after she had an affair

17:47.232 --> 17:49.026
and raised his son, Gyeong-seo, alone.

17:49.109 --> 17:51.737
Two years ago
while Cho went to the bathroom,

17:51.820 --> 17:55.699
his unattended son climbed on a desk, fell
through a torn window screen, and died.

17:56.867 --> 18:00.746
His ex-wife reported him
for child neglect,

18:00.829 --> 18:06.001
but the court ruled that he didn't neglect
his parental duties despite his busy work.

18:06.585 --> 18:10.506
I don't see anything unusual so far.

18:11.256 --> 18:16.345
I wonder why he kidnapped children
and murdered one after losing his own son.

18:20.891 --> 18:21.934
We're back to square one.

18:23.435 --> 18:25.729
What do we have about the case?

18:26.271 --> 18:30.150
The police took these photos at the scene
when his son fell to his death.

18:35.656 --> 18:38.700
His son must've loved pizza.

18:38.784 --> 18:41.829
He diligently collected coupons
and even drew some.

18:41.912 --> 18:44.414
He drew fake coupons?

18:44.498 --> 18:48.418
It could be more like
he wanted to win a prize.

18:48.502 --> 18:50.129
What were the prizes?

18:50.921 --> 18:52.673
-That's it!
-What?

18:54.341 --> 18:57.928
A six-year-old boy collected coupons
over a kimchi refrigerator?

18:58.929 --> 19:00.097
No way.

19:00.180 --> 19:02.015
Hold on. Let's see. When was it?

19:02.099 --> 19:03.142
Three or so years ago,

19:03.225 --> 19:06.395
a neighborhood supermarket hosted a prize
festival to celebrate their grand opening.

19:07.396 --> 19:11.733
Da-bong won a television, the first prize.

19:12.234 --> 19:14.319
But she cried.

19:15.028 --> 19:15.863
Why?

19:15.946 --> 19:20.200
Because she wanted the fifth prize,
a cartoon-character backpack.

19:21.702 --> 19:24.746
How children think is totally different
from how adults think.

19:26.039 --> 19:29.376
Then, from a child's perspective…

19:31.753 --> 19:32.671
What about this one?

19:33.964 --> 19:34.882
I think that's it.

19:35.465 --> 19:37.801
Children love camping.

19:39.428 --> 19:41.597
I want to go camping.

19:41.680 --> 19:45.851
He stopped me, saying he'd take me
somewhere fun the next day.

19:45.934 --> 19:49.646
Cho Chi-yeong told Si-ho
that they'd go somewhere fun the next day.

19:49.730 --> 19:51.732
It may have been a camping site.

19:52.482 --> 19:56.361
Si-ho said that Cho Chi-yeong
gave a safety lesson at school.

19:56.445 --> 20:01.450
What if he was seeking a target
at the time?

20:02.075 --> 20:05.162
And what if he wanted
to give himself a chance?

20:07.080 --> 20:09.333
To himself who couldn't protect his son?

20:09.416 --> 20:13.170
In fact, he called Ye-jun his son.

20:13.253 --> 20:16.131
And he fed Ye-jun pizza,
which was his son's favorite.

20:16.215 --> 20:17.925
So, in short,

20:18.008 --> 20:19.551
he didn't look for a target of revenge,

20:19.635 --> 20:22.804
but a chance for himself to be a good dad?

20:22.888 --> 20:24.556
He's a total lunatic.

20:24.640 --> 20:27.309
If he was going to take Si-ho

20:27.392 --> 20:29.603
to the camping site
his son wanted to go to,

20:29.686 --> 20:32.564
he may have buried Si-ho there.

20:33.148 --> 20:34.900
It's plausible, but it's a little…

20:34.983 --> 20:36.151
Uncertain. I know.

20:36.693 --> 20:38.695
So, I'm going to ask him in person.

20:39.780 --> 20:41.782
I doubt he'll agree to meet you.

20:41.865 --> 20:43.242
He won't talk to me,

20:44.618 --> 20:47.204
but he'll talk to Si-ho.

20:56.797 --> 20:59.716
CHO CHI-YEONG

20:59.800 --> 21:01.551
TO: SEOUL CORRECTIONAL FACILITY

21:01.635 --> 21:03.428
FROM: SECOND FLOOR OF
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

21:19.945 --> 21:21.780
To Mr. Detective.

21:22.531 --> 21:25.200
Mister, this is Si-ho.

21:25.867 --> 21:28.870
The Yoon Si-ho that you said
had a nice, round head.

21:29.871 --> 21:33.792
We played word chain
and cops and robbers together.

21:34.459 --> 21:37.587
You showed me your pistol too.

21:37.671 --> 21:38.880
Do you remember?

21:41.383 --> 21:43.927
Cho Chi-yeong may stay silent
until the end.

21:44.011 --> 21:47.180
Can you look for Si-ho's body
at the camping site with Bong-su?

21:47.764 --> 21:48.682
Okay.

21:55.939 --> 22:01.778
GOOD SLEEPING CAMPING SITE

22:03.739 --> 22:07.909
We have only one person from the police?

22:07.993 --> 22:10.162
I barely got my day off to come here too.

22:10.746 --> 22:12.331
We still lack evidence.

22:13.457 --> 22:17.294
Even so, why can't they
just believe what the hero says?

22:17.377 --> 22:18.545
My point exactly.

22:20.547 --> 22:22.549
This place is so big.
Will we be able to find him?

22:23.300 --> 22:24.259
We must.

22:25.135 --> 22:27.179
Everything is possible with God.

22:27.262 --> 22:28.597
There are just four of us,

22:29.181 --> 22:32.642
but he will give us the ability
of 40 or even 400.

22:36.980 --> 22:39.191
Let me give you some precautions first.

22:39.983 --> 22:43.278
Plant growth is different
at the burial site due to organic matter.

22:43.361 --> 22:47.365
So pay attention to areas
with uneven growth or unusual coloring.

22:47.449 --> 22:50.827
And I sent each of you
a metal-detecting app.

22:50.911 --> 22:52.537
Hold your phones close to the ground

22:52.621 --> 22:56.625
and they react to things
like buttons, keys, or zippers.

22:58.710 --> 23:00.962
Attorney Han and Father,

23:01.671 --> 23:03.256
please search that side.

23:03.340 --> 23:05.634
You and I will search this side.

23:05.717 --> 23:06.718
Okay.

23:07.677 --> 23:09.262
Are you a police officer?

23:16.228 --> 23:17.354
Shall we?

23:18.980 --> 23:20.107
I'll do my best.

23:37.124 --> 23:38.333
It's you again.

23:40.752 --> 23:42.045
Who are you, really?

23:46.216 --> 23:47.467
Who are you

23:48.343 --> 23:50.262
to send me such a letter?

23:55.767 --> 23:57.144
Si-ho is…

23:59.146 --> 24:00.397
here right now.

24:04.151 --> 24:05.277
What are you saying?

24:05.360 --> 24:09.239
Otherwise, how else would I know
what happened between you and him?

24:12.033 --> 24:13.285
Stop lying.

24:14.828 --> 24:16.246
Stop messing around.

24:16.329 --> 24:18.748
You kidnapped Ye-jun and Si-ho.

24:20.250 --> 24:21.835
And you caused Si-ho to die.

24:23.253 --> 24:26.256
Anyone can see
you're a despicable criminal.

24:26.339 --> 24:27.924
But I think…

24:30.552 --> 24:31.845
you as Gyeong-seo's dad…

24:34.097 --> 24:36.600
would be a little different.

24:45.859 --> 24:49.196
Please, Gyeong-seo's father.

24:50.071 --> 24:52.157
Think of Si-ho's parents.

24:52.991 --> 24:55.285
Unable to find their beloved son's body,

24:56.494 --> 24:58.830
they're living in utter despair.

25:01.333 --> 25:03.168
You know how it feels to lose a child.

25:03.251 --> 25:04.419
Shut your trap.

25:06.463 --> 25:08.006
You must've wanted to be forgiven.

25:09.424 --> 25:11.009
After Gyeong-seo died,

25:12.302 --> 25:14.262
you must've had so many regrets.

25:15.388 --> 25:19.226
So you tried to prove that you weren't
a bad dad and ease your guilt

25:19.309 --> 25:22.812
by doing what you couldn't do
to your son with those children.

25:22.896 --> 25:25.941
-Shut up!
-For such an absurd reason,

25:26.024 --> 25:29.236
you gave Ye-jun an unforgettable trauma,
let Si-ho die,

25:30.487 --> 25:31.780
and devastated their parents.

25:31.863 --> 25:33.406
What do you know?

25:36.493 --> 25:37.577
I know…

25:40.247 --> 25:41.831
that parents mean the world…

25:43.625 --> 25:45.168
to their children.

25:50.340 --> 25:53.468
You robbed those children of everything.

26:12.904 --> 26:14.322
I don't know who Si-ho is.

26:16.324 --> 26:20.203
And if his parents really loved him,

26:22.622 --> 26:24.582
they wouldn't have left him alone.

26:26.042 --> 26:27.502
Such parents…

26:29.129 --> 26:30.839
don't deserve to be parents.

26:38.013 --> 26:40.598
Don't say that about my mom and dad.

26:42.517 --> 26:44.936
My parents

26:45.020 --> 26:46.688
loved me.

26:47.355 --> 26:49.316
They did everything for me.

26:50.817 --> 26:52.902
To buy me delicious food,

26:53.528 --> 26:55.613
my mom saved on buying make up.

26:56.573 --> 26:59.451
My dad worked until late at night

27:00.160 --> 27:02.245
to buy me a pair of cute rain boots.

27:03.413 --> 27:07.250
They're the one and only parents I have.

27:08.501 --> 27:10.712
I love them so much.

27:12.047 --> 27:15.967
I wouldn't trade them
for a hundred pizzas.

27:16.051 --> 27:20.597
I wouldn't trade them
even for an amusement park.

27:26.144 --> 27:27.854
Mister…

27:29.397 --> 27:31.775
why are you trying to trade him?

27:35.153 --> 27:37.447
I'm not your son.

27:40.575 --> 27:45.288
He must've loved you so much too.

27:49.584 --> 27:52.128
If I were your son,

27:53.046 --> 27:54.964
I'd be sad.

28:00.470 --> 28:01.930
Mister.

28:03.390 --> 28:04.891
Why are you crying?

28:07.769 --> 28:08.728
I…

28:11.189 --> 28:13.441
I wanted to do my best for Gyeong-seo.

28:16.361 --> 28:18.571
It felt like my fault
that he was separated from his mom

28:20.448 --> 28:22.659
and that he was left alone.

28:27.122 --> 28:28.456
If I had another chance…

28:29.707 --> 28:32.502
I thought I'd do better
if I had another chance.

28:42.929 --> 28:44.973
I didn't know you were that sick.

28:46.182 --> 28:47.809
I thought you simply had a fever.

28:49.102 --> 28:51.062
You were dead
when I came back the next morning.

28:52.272 --> 28:54.274
I was utterly shocked.

28:58.445 --> 28:59.571
I'm sorry.

29:02.407 --> 29:04.284
I'm truly sorry.

29:05.034 --> 29:05.952
Truly.

29:07.704 --> 29:09.706
If you're truly sorry,

29:11.416 --> 29:13.668
bring me back to my parents.

29:16.838 --> 29:19.799
Where am I right now?

29:36.858 --> 29:38.109
-Check here.
-Yes, sir.

29:38.193 --> 29:39.611
On the right.

29:53.082 --> 29:54.042
What?

30:06.179 --> 30:07.806
Si-ho…

30:15.271 --> 30:16.481
Are you sure about this?

30:18.733 --> 30:21.861
They both said they were ready.

30:24.113 --> 30:25.615
What about Si-ho, though?

30:26.533 --> 30:28.868
He's going to see his parents
on awkward terms.

30:29.786 --> 30:32.705
Still, they're his parents.

30:56.145 --> 30:58.147
Shall we go?

30:59.440 --> 31:00.608
Yes.

32:13.806 --> 32:14.933
Si-ho.

32:16.684 --> 32:18.519
Mommy's late.

32:21.439 --> 32:22.440
I'm sorry.

32:28.154 --> 32:31.157
YOON SI-HO

32:33.534 --> 32:35.328
Have you been well, sweetheart?

32:41.292 --> 32:42.293
Si-ho.

32:44.087 --> 32:45.380
Your mommy's here.

32:46.631 --> 32:47.924
You missed her, didn't you?

32:49.968 --> 32:51.678
Oh, wow.

32:52.220 --> 32:53.429
There are so many flowers.

32:55.306 --> 32:57.350
You must've had a lot of friends come by.

32:58.977 --> 33:00.228
Si-ho…

33:28.423 --> 33:29.674
Mom!

33:30.633 --> 33:31.467
Dad!

33:31.551 --> 33:32.552
-Si-ho.
-Si-ho!

33:32.635 --> 33:33.761
Si-ho!

33:34.637 --> 33:35.805
Si-ho, come here.

33:41.436 --> 33:43.980
Our dear Si-ho's here.

33:50.069 --> 33:51.154
That was a low jump.

34:04.333 --> 34:05.918
It's time for me to go, isn't it?

34:10.757 --> 34:12.300
How did you know?

34:12.383 --> 34:15.470
Your sad face tells me so.

34:18.306 --> 34:19.307
But mister,

34:20.516 --> 34:22.060
don't be sad.

34:23.478 --> 34:27.190
I'm so happy that I got to see
my parents get along.

34:28.941 --> 34:30.109
So

34:30.860 --> 34:32.070
smile, mister.

34:37.450 --> 34:39.243
Thank you so much.

34:39.744 --> 34:44.916
You're a hundred, a thousand times
cooler than Lightning Man.

34:49.295 --> 34:50.171
I am?

34:52.131 --> 34:54.926
What's so cool about me?

34:55.510 --> 34:56.552
You're kind.

34:57.512 --> 34:58.930
You're handsome.

35:02.600 --> 35:03.684
And you're super weak.

35:05.812 --> 35:07.063
What's that supposed to mean?

35:07.146 --> 35:11.400
It's really hard for someone weak
to save others, you know.

35:13.986 --> 35:14.987
Then,

35:15.738 --> 35:18.157
does that mean
I pulled off something that difficult?

35:18.241 --> 35:19.534
Yes.

35:19.617 --> 35:25.498
You're so cool that your dad must
also be proud of you up above.

35:30.461 --> 35:32.588
Thanks, Lightning Man.

35:34.674 --> 35:36.509
You were so cool too.

35:40.429 --> 35:41.722
Si-ho,

35:42.557 --> 35:44.642
I prepared a farewell gift for you.

35:45.226 --> 35:46.394
What?

35:46.477 --> 35:49.188
One, two,

35:50.231 --> 35:51.149
three!

35:54.360 --> 35:57.446
-Lightning power.
-Lightning power.

36:02.034 --> 36:05.204
Lightning power!

36:07.373 --> 36:10.251
-Lightning power!
-Lightning power!

36:16.716 --> 36:18.134
Goodbye, Si-ho.

36:54.837 --> 36:58.799
I-rang, I'm so glad you recovered quickly.

36:58.883 --> 37:00.593
I-rang has great stamina. That's for sure.

37:00.676 --> 37:02.094
-I know. Gosh.
-Bong-su.

37:02.178 --> 37:05.181
-Thank you for the meal.
-Help yourself.

37:05.264 --> 37:08.643
Why don't we have a toast
to I-rang's good health?

37:08.726 --> 37:10.978
-Okay. Cheers!
-All right.

37:11.520 --> 37:14.607
-You too, Da-bong. Cheers!
-Cheers!

37:28.204 --> 37:30.665
-What?
-Eat as you drink.

37:34.126 --> 37:34.961
Okay.

37:36.003 --> 37:37.672
Don't just smile, eat.

37:44.929 --> 37:47.598
Why are you only giving I-rang
special treatment?

37:48.975 --> 37:49.892
Well, I…

37:51.560 --> 37:54.563
He's my only colleague.
I should look out for him.

37:54.647 --> 37:57.108
You're hurting my feelings.

37:57.191 --> 37:59.110
I did the best I could to help you too.

37:59.193 --> 38:01.612
You didn't just help us.

38:01.696 --> 38:06.742
You're an irreplaceable asset to us.

38:06.826 --> 38:09.370
You're like a paralegal, so to speak.

38:10.288 --> 38:11.914
-Oh, my.
-Right?

38:12.665 --> 38:14.709
Yes, our paralegal.

38:14.792 --> 38:17.461
An actual paralegal, not a role?

38:17.545 --> 38:19.046
Yes, of course.

38:19.130 --> 38:21.882
Mr. Paralegal, let me pour you some.

38:23.259 --> 38:24.135
Goodness.

38:24.218 --> 38:30.141
Cheers to the first paralegal
of Shin I-rang Law Office!

38:30.725 --> 38:32.977
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

38:33.060 --> 38:34.895
I'm a paralegal!

38:41.527 --> 38:42.820
Eat up.

38:48.326 --> 38:50.244
ATTORNEY SHIN
INITIATES A LAWSUIT

38:50.328 --> 38:52.246
ON BEHALF OF
VICTIM YOON SI-HO'S FAMILY

39:00.463 --> 39:01.714
THE VICTIM'S FATHER,
YOON JAE-UK,

39:01.797 --> 39:03.132
FILED A SUIT AGAINST
CHO CHI-YEONG

39:03.215 --> 39:04.467
AND RETAINED
ATTORNEY SHIN I-RANG

39:04.550 --> 39:05.551
AS A LEGAL REPRESENTATIVE

39:10.639 --> 39:13.684
PETITION FOR TORT DAMAGES

39:22.651 --> 39:26.197
TAEBAEK

39:29.450 --> 39:31.410
I need to go to him!

39:35.373 --> 39:36.457
Come in.

39:41.629 --> 39:42.880
Mail for you, sir.

39:45.674 --> 39:46.509
What's that?

39:48.177 --> 39:50.679
It's mail from overseas for the Chairman.

39:52.348 --> 39:53.724
Give it to me. I'll hand it to him.

39:53.808 --> 39:54.725
Yes, sir.

40:00.940 --> 40:02.942
It's where Father got operated.

40:35.349 --> 40:36.684
I'll get going now.

40:36.767 --> 40:38.936
-Be careful on your way home.
-Visit us often.

40:39.603 --> 40:42.940
Pretty auntie, goodbye.

40:43.023 --> 40:44.066
Bye.

40:44.608 --> 40:45.693
Mr. Paralegal.

40:47.862 --> 40:49.947
I'll walk her home and come back.

40:50.531 --> 40:52.116
Don't come back.

40:52.700 --> 40:54.243
Take care.

40:54.326 --> 40:55.327
Bye-bye.

40:57.455 --> 40:59.290
Let's go back inside now.

40:59.832 --> 41:00.791
I feel so good.

41:01.876 --> 41:03.002
Our dear paralegal.

41:03.711 --> 41:04.628
That's right.

41:10.092 --> 41:11.385
Do you have anything to say?

41:12.595 --> 41:13.429
Excuse me?

41:14.054 --> 41:15.598
Like what?

41:16.724 --> 41:20.060
Back at Haneul Park and the hospital,

41:21.145 --> 41:22.605
you tried to tell me something.

41:32.740 --> 41:33.699
What are you doing?

41:35.826 --> 41:37.912
Watching out for ghosts.

41:37.995 --> 41:40.581
They always show up
during important moments.

41:43.125 --> 41:47.129
Then, why don't we meet up
somewhere ghosts don't know?

41:48.631 --> 41:50.257
Let's eat something delicious

41:50.799 --> 41:52.092
and say what we have to say.

41:53.677 --> 41:56.555
Do you also have something to tell me?

41:57.264 --> 41:58.182
Of course.

42:01.685 --> 42:04.897
Did I perhaps make a mistake?

42:04.980 --> 42:06.524
It's not like that.

42:07.066 --> 42:07.942
Wait.

42:08.651 --> 42:09.652
Maybe it is.

42:10.486 --> 42:11.403
Is it?

42:12.613 --> 42:14.740
What did I do wrong this time?

42:17.868 --> 42:21.580
Attorney Han,
it's better to rip the band-aid off.

42:21.664 --> 42:23.249
Can't you just tell me now?

42:23.791 --> 42:24.750
I don't want to.

42:25.501 --> 42:27.086
Come on. Just tell me.

42:28.879 --> 42:29.838
Geez.

42:41.475 --> 42:43.644
I'm late but happy birthday.

42:44.395 --> 42:47.106
I wanted to celebrate it for you
although it already passed.

42:54.697 --> 42:56.198
I finally get to give these to her.

43:21.432 --> 43:22.850
Attorney Shin I-rang?

43:24.351 --> 43:26.854
Hello, Attorney Han Na-hyun.

43:28.480 --> 43:30.316
Are you working outside?

43:30.399 --> 43:31.233
Yes.

43:31.317 --> 43:34.445
I'm on my way to get a signature
on the notice of retention from Mr. Yoon.

43:35.613 --> 43:37.698
What are you up to?

43:38.407 --> 43:42.745
CEO Kang of Ideal Shoes has asked me
to go over a contract.

43:42.828 --> 43:45.080
He's signing a new contract
with an online platform.

43:45.164 --> 43:47.499
I see. That's good.

43:50.836 --> 43:52.796
You still remember our plans
later today, right?

43:53.422 --> 43:54.923
I texted you the address.

43:55.507 --> 43:56.884
Yes, I got it.

43:58.135 --> 44:00.679
I'll be there by 8:00 p.m.

44:01.347 --> 44:03.474
Okay, see you later.

44:24.536 --> 44:26.038
You seem to be in a happy mood.

44:30.626 --> 44:31.960
YOON SI-HO

44:34.463 --> 44:36.882
Attorney Shin must be here.

44:43.597 --> 44:45.265
YANG DO-KYUNG

44:45.349 --> 44:46.433
Come in.

44:49.186 --> 44:50.062
Are you busy?

44:51.188 --> 44:53.732
-No, Father.
-Let's eat together if you haven't yet.

45:23.554 --> 45:27.224
The number cannot be reached.
You'll be directed to voicemail after…

45:27.307 --> 45:28.434
That's strange.

45:29.435 --> 45:30.686
Did he go somewhere?

45:37.568 --> 45:38.485
You were inside.

45:38.569 --> 45:40.863
I was worried
because you didn't answer your phone.

45:40.946 --> 45:42.656
I'm dropping the case.

45:43.449 --> 45:44.283
Leave.

45:46.034 --> 45:47.995
-Excuse me?
-I don't want to talk to you.

45:49.413 --> 45:50.581
So, leave.

45:51.248 --> 45:52.124
Wait.

45:52.916 --> 45:56.211
Mr. Yoon, did something happen?

45:57.796 --> 46:00.132
I'm really grateful
to you for finding Si-ho.

46:02.176 --> 46:04.344
And I know that you've done nothing wrong.

46:05.888 --> 46:08.807
But the thought of your father
makes me shudder.

46:09.808 --> 46:11.477
Because of Shin Gi-jung, my father…

46:14.855 --> 46:15.898
Please just go.

46:23.614 --> 46:26.742
It's been a long time
since we had a meal together like this.

46:28.243 --> 46:29.119
I know.

46:29.703 --> 46:32.122
When I was healthy, I was busy with work.

46:32.706 --> 46:36.585
And when I had time,
I was sick and away from home.

46:38.170 --> 46:41.548
Now that you're healthy again,
let's do this more often.

46:42.132 --> 46:42.966
Okay.

46:47.679 --> 46:51.475
Don't you have to revisit the hospital
in the States, then?

46:51.558 --> 46:53.477
No, since my treatment is over.

46:55.562 --> 46:56.438
Right.

46:58.607 --> 47:00.150
My illness made me realize

47:01.401 --> 47:02.945
what was most precious.

47:03.946 --> 47:05.656
Money, reputation, status…

47:06.240 --> 47:07.449
None of it matters.

47:08.951 --> 47:10.410
In the end,

47:11.662 --> 47:12.871
family is all you have.

47:15.332 --> 47:16.416
Your grandpa…

47:18.252 --> 47:20.629
was never one to commend me.

47:21.880 --> 47:24.675
He always asked
if it was the best I could do.

47:25.842 --> 47:26.843
And every time,

47:27.886 --> 47:30.013
I answered I'd try harder.

47:31.515 --> 47:35.477
I couldn't be a warm father to you
because that was how I was raised.

47:38.814 --> 47:40.315
But I'm sure about one thing.

47:41.400 --> 47:44.111
I will protect you no matter what.

47:45.404 --> 47:46.655
That's family.

47:47.698 --> 47:50.033
I believe you'll do the same.

47:53.829 --> 47:56.623
Do you trust me?

47:56.707 --> 47:57.708
Yes.

47:58.792 --> 48:00.377
I trust my son.

48:04.923 --> 48:06.425
Don't worry, Father.

48:07.551 --> 48:08.927
I'll protect you.

48:12.389 --> 48:13.724
All right.

48:13.807 --> 48:14.641
Let's eat.

48:38.081 --> 48:42.085
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

48:44.379 --> 48:47.466
But the thought of your father
makes me shudder.

48:48.634 --> 48:50.636
Because of Shin Gi-jung, my father…

49:05.192 --> 49:06.902
PROSECUTOR KIM HYEON-U

49:12.783 --> 49:13.700
Hello, Prosecutor Kim.

49:13.784 --> 49:19.039
Attorney Shin, are you free to talk?
This is about Mr. Yoon Jae-uk's case.

49:20.332 --> 49:21.875
I don't think

49:21.958 --> 49:24.002
I can take on that case.

49:25.671 --> 49:29.174
Mr. Yoon is dismissing the lawsuit.

49:30.425 --> 49:32.135
He did? Why?

49:32.719 --> 49:35.597
I'm not so sure.

49:37.849 --> 49:38.767
Could you

49:39.601 --> 49:42.312
tell me what his father's name is?

49:42.896 --> 49:44.481
Just a moment.

49:50.862 --> 49:52.239
His name is Yoon Dae-myeong.

49:52.989 --> 49:54.991
He passed away in 2003.

49:55.701 --> 49:57.661
Why do you ask about him?

49:58.370 --> 50:00.205
There's something I have to find out.

50:01.373 --> 50:02.416
Thank you.

50:17.514 --> 50:19.266
YOON DAE-MYEONG,
SHIN GI-JUNG, 2003

50:22.978 --> 50:24.730
EXCESSIVE PUNISHMENT FOR
CHARGES OF CHILD SEXUAL ABUSE

50:24.813 --> 50:25.814
WARRANT DISMISSED

50:29.776 --> 50:30.819
PROSECUTOR SHIN
SEEKS WARRANT AGAIN

50:30.902 --> 50:31.987
FOR YOON DAE-MYEONG
SEXUAL ASSAULT CASE

50:33.739 --> 50:35.949
YOON DAE-MYEONG'S SUICIDE…
CRITICISM OF UNDUE PROSECUTION…

50:40.495 --> 50:42.873
CORRUPT PROSECUTOR SHIN GI-JUNG
DIES IN A CAR ACCIDENT

50:58.263 --> 50:59.264
It's in.

51:10.275 --> 51:11.818
Okay, good job.

51:19.326 --> 51:22.621
I need to know what's going on
if I'm to protect you, Father.

51:56.655 --> 51:59.074
Why didn't you go home?

52:04.120 --> 52:06.289
Why were you spacing out here?

52:09.876 --> 52:11.586
I want to know the truth,

52:13.964 --> 52:17.259
but I'm clueless
no matter how many articles I read.

52:22.222 --> 52:23.056
What happened

52:24.349 --> 52:26.142
to your father?

52:28.645 --> 52:29.604
What did

52:31.147 --> 52:32.315
my father do?

52:33.316 --> 52:35.527
It's too late to talk about it now.

52:37.279 --> 52:38.989
Both our fathers are

52:40.824 --> 52:42.450
already dead.

52:44.286 --> 52:45.161
Even so,

52:46.121 --> 52:47.289
I want to know.

52:48.331 --> 52:49.249
Actually,

52:51.084 --> 52:52.252
I need to know.

52:54.045 --> 52:55.088
Please tell me.

53:05.974 --> 53:08.059
My father was an educator.

53:09.978 --> 53:12.939
He was Teacher of the Year
as many as 4 times in 25 years.

53:13.982 --> 53:16.610
He was a diligent and respected teacher.

53:18.194 --> 53:19.946
But in the year he became vice-principal,

53:20.989 --> 53:22.365
something happened.

53:26.453 --> 53:28.830
There was group bullying at school.

53:28.914 --> 53:30.040
Come on, get up!

53:30.123 --> 53:34.169
My father imposed the severest penalty
possible on the bully, expulsion.

53:34.252 --> 53:35.545
One more time.

53:35.629 --> 53:37.005
It's a dud.

53:37.088 --> 53:38.924
The bully student's parents

53:39.007 --> 53:41.843
sued my father
for excessive and biased punishment.

53:42.844 --> 53:46.139
But the court dismissed it
on presumption of innocence.

53:48.308 --> 53:49.976
The real problem started from here.

53:51.603 --> 53:53.188
The prosecutor in charge,

53:55.065 --> 53:58.902
Shin Gi-jung, conducted
a fishing expedition

53:58.985 --> 54:01.696
and prosecuted my father
for totally irrelevant charges.

54:06.076 --> 54:07.452
PROSECUTOR SHIN GI-JUNG

54:08.036 --> 54:08.870
Yes.

54:10.330 --> 54:11.581
Let's go with it, then.

54:17.379 --> 54:21.341
He prosecuted him for property speculation
over his capital gains.

54:27.180 --> 54:30.642
For the embezzlement of operation funds
over a missing lunch receipt.

54:30.725 --> 54:32.394
Let's see.

54:32.477 --> 54:34.437
INCHEON DISTRICT COURT
TO YOON DAE-MYEONG

54:35.313 --> 54:39.901
And for sexual harassment over a simple
reminder enforcing the dress code.

54:42.946 --> 54:45.448
INCHEON DISTRICT COURT
TO YOON DAE-MYEONG

54:49.953 --> 54:51.579
Most of the prosecutions were dismissed,

54:52.205 --> 54:55.959
but my father could barely go to work
due to the legal battles.

54:57.293 --> 54:58.878
And to pay for the growing legal fees,

55:00.338 --> 55:02.716
he even lost the one house he had.

55:02.799 --> 55:05.593
Why to that extent, though?

55:08.179 --> 55:09.305
Did your father…

55:10.724 --> 55:13.143
have something to do
with my father before that?

55:13.727 --> 55:15.311
I was curious too,

55:17.188 --> 55:20.191
but it all made sense when I heard
what my father's attorney said.

55:21.067 --> 55:22.777
He explained that when prosecutors resign,

55:23.361 --> 55:26.406
they are often recruited by law firms
for their ties to the prosecution.

55:28.283 --> 55:33.288
And that the bully student's father was
the head of Korea's top law firm.

55:35.123 --> 55:36.416
Prosecutor Shin Gi-jung

55:37.208 --> 55:39.252
used my father as a sacrificial lamb.

55:40.336 --> 55:41.880
For his own good,

55:45.008 --> 55:47.385
he drove my father to death.

55:57.937 --> 55:58.938
My father

56:00.315 --> 56:03.902
was found dead in the back alley
of Chinatown in Incheon.

56:05.278 --> 56:09.032
A will and a half-burnt charcoal briquette
were found in his car.

56:10.742 --> 56:12.786
One sentence was written on the will.

56:14.829 --> 56:16.039
"Apologies…

56:19.501 --> 56:20.627
to my family."

56:25.173 --> 56:26.674
Three months later,

56:30.261 --> 56:32.639
my mother also took her own life.

56:47.237 --> 56:48.613
All this time,

56:51.866 --> 56:54.494
I completely turned a blind eye…

56:56.371 --> 56:58.414
to what my father did.

57:01.334 --> 57:04.754
I thought that
my family and I were the only victims.

57:08.299 --> 57:09.467
Now I see that…

57:12.804 --> 57:14.472
I've been selfish.

57:16.516 --> 57:19.269
I've forgotten that
a lot of people are still in pain

57:20.937 --> 57:22.105
because of him.

57:31.156 --> 57:35.243
I know my apology won't change anything,

57:37.162 --> 57:38.121
but…

57:39.831 --> 57:41.166
I'm deeply sorry.

58:07.150 --> 58:08.526
So, did you find the shaman?

58:09.152 --> 58:11.696
Please wait a little.
I'll be able to find him soon.

58:13.156 --> 58:14.240
You need to hurry.

58:14.324 --> 58:19.245
If the shaman summoned ghosts
and Shin I-rang has been seeing them,

58:21.706 --> 58:24.959
he may see him too.

58:25.543 --> 58:26.669
Yes, sir.

58:26.753 --> 58:27.712
Him?

58:58.826 --> 59:02.163
SHIN I-RANG, HAN NA-HYUN

59:34.237 --> 59:35.488
Who are you?

59:38.116 --> 59:39.993
How may I help you?

01:00:20.533 --> 01:00:22.368
I didn't mean to surprise you.

01:00:23.453 --> 01:00:24.454
I'm sorry.

01:00:29.709 --> 01:00:30.585
How…

01:00:30.668 --> 01:00:32.128
I'm not sure myself.

01:00:33.004 --> 01:00:36.841
Something just drew me here.

01:00:38.635 --> 01:00:39.552
Why…

01:00:41.137 --> 01:00:42.221
now?

01:00:48.102 --> 01:00:49.520
It is a bit late.

01:00:50.104 --> 01:00:52.106
I'll come again early tomorrow.

01:01:01.074 --> 01:01:02.450
I can't take it.

01:01:05.745 --> 01:01:07.664
-Excuse me?
-I…

01:01:11.793 --> 01:01:13.002
will not…

01:01:16.005 --> 01:01:17.548
accept your case.

01:01:34.148 --> 01:01:35.108
SPECIAL THANKS TO CHOI WON-YOUNG

01:01:40.488 --> 01:01:43.408
CORRUPT PROSECUTOR SHIN GI-JUNG
DIES IN A CAR ACCIDENT

01:01:50.915 --> 01:01:53.167
EPILOGUE

01:01:55.128 --> 01:01:56.129
Happy birthday.

01:02:32.457 --> 01:02:33.708
A new ghost came?

01:02:33.791 --> 01:02:35.585
I guess he isn't
on good terms with that ghost.

01:02:35.668 --> 01:02:36.544
Why now?

01:02:36.627 --> 01:02:38.421
Do you perhaps know who I am?

01:02:38.504 --> 01:02:40.506
You are someone who can never be forgiven.

01:02:40.590 --> 01:02:42.884
The prosecutor in charge was Shin Gi-jung.

01:02:42.967 --> 01:02:45.094
I know it's late,
but shouldn't we reveal the truth?

01:02:45.178 --> 01:02:48.264
I have no idea about myself
except for the fact that I'm dead.

01:02:48.347 --> 01:02:50.683
I'm calling about a ghost
who needs to pass on.

01:02:50.767 --> 01:02:53.311
-Was I that nasty?
-I'll have to send him off myself.

01:02:53.394 --> 01:02:54.896
-He left?
-He left.

01:02:54.979 --> 01:02:56.022
Don't resent me.

01:02:56.105 --> 01:03:01.110
Subtitle translation by: Eunjin Erica Kim
